WEBVTT

01:46.433 --> 01:49.333
- Ask any tow-headed schoolboy
how many senses we got,

01:49.400 --> 01:52.300
and it's likely
they're gonna say five.

01:52.367 --> 01:53.333
Five?

01:53.400 --> 01:54.934
Are you kiddin' me?

01:55.000 --> 01:57.767
What about my sense of balance,
entitlement, fair play?

01:57.834 --> 01:59.400
Problem is,

01:59.467 --> 02:02.367
five is about the most our
tiny little brains can handle.

02:02.433 --> 02:05.300
But sometimes we have
so many senses cluttering us up,

02:05.367 --> 02:07.266
so many ways to feel
about a thing,

02:07.333 --> 02:09.867
we blow a fuse.

02:09.934 --> 02:11.300
And what's that lead to?

02:11.367 --> 02:13.133
Senseless violence.

02:13.200 --> 02:16.700
Yeah, senseless violence,

02:16.767 --> 02:19.033
comes in all shapes
and colors.

02:19.100 --> 02:21.066
- For a second day,

02:21.133 --> 02:23.400
riots have rocked
the east side of the city,

02:23.467 --> 02:26.300
ignited by Governor Devlin's
comment that he would pardon

02:26.367 --> 02:29.133
Mayor Wilson Loewen
if Loewen is convicted

02:29.200 --> 02:31.200
for his role
in the 1963 murder

02:31.266 --> 02:34.133
of two small
African-American girls.

02:34.200 --> 02:36.100
In response
to the rioting,

02:36.166 --> 02:37.867
city schools
and offices are closed.

02:37.934 --> 02:39.633
All state correctional
facilities

02:39.700 --> 02:41.166
are under tight security.

02:41.233 --> 02:44.266
A verdict is expected
sometime this week.

02:46.367 --> 02:48.333
- Guard, guard!

02:48.400 --> 02:50.300
Aah!

02:50.367 --> 02:52.533
No!

02:52.600 --> 02:54.066
- Your father was stabbed
with an ice pick,

02:54.133 --> 02:57.367
once in the back,
several times in the stomach.

03:00.500 --> 03:01.834
- Who?

03:01.900 --> 03:03.400
Who murdered my dad?

03:03.467 --> 03:05.900
- We're investigating,
searching cells for evidence,

03:05.967 --> 03:07.633
for the murder weapon.

03:09.333 --> 03:11.033
- Man, this is bullshit.

03:15.800 --> 03:18.600
- I--I want to go
to the funeral.

03:18.667 --> 03:20.800
- I'm sorry,
we can't permit that.

03:20.867 --> 03:22.266
We're in lockdown.

03:22.333 --> 03:25.333
- But warden, my parole hearing
is tomorrow,

03:25.400 --> 03:27.467
and there's
a fairly good chance

03:27.533 --> 03:29.333
that I'm gonna
go free anyway.

03:29.400 --> 03:33.300
- Because of the riots,
your hearing has been postponed.

03:34.300 --> 03:37.700
- Guess what we found.

03:38.867 --> 03:40.066
- But why?

03:40.133 --> 03:42.233
Why would Clarence Seroy
kill my father?

03:42.300 --> 03:43.900
I don't know Seroy;
it makes no sense.

03:43.967 --> 03:47.066
- This is Oz, Beecher,
and nothing makes sense.

03:47.133 --> 03:48.934
Maybe it's these riots.

03:49.000 --> 03:50.867
There's a lot of
racial tension out there.

03:50.934 --> 03:55.734
- No, more likely,
the Aryans hired Seroy,

03:55.800 --> 03:59.266
or planted the ice pick
in his cell to throw Glynn off.

03:59.333 --> 04:03.834
This is fucking
Schillinger's doing.

04:03.900 --> 04:06.066
- Killing Beecher's father,
man, what a rush.

04:06.133 --> 04:09.200
It's better than
a case of Red Bull.

04:09.266 --> 04:12.166
The fuckin' hacks haven't
a clue who did the deed.

04:13.266 --> 04:15.600
Hey, Clarence,
how's it going?

04:15.667 --> 04:16.734
- Man, this is bullshit.

04:18.867 --> 04:20.667
- They'll never
figure out who did it.

04:20.734 --> 04:22.300
- Shut the fuck up!

04:22.367 --> 04:24.300
- The jury found Mayor
Wilson Loewen guilty

04:24.367 --> 04:26.767
of murder in
the second degree.

04:27.867 --> 04:28.900
- Fuck!

04:33.000 --> 04:34.667
- I believe that
Mayor Loewen is innocent

04:34.734 --> 04:38.767
and I believe that this trial
was a mockery of justice.

04:38.834 --> 04:43.633
However, due to the volatility
of the situation,

04:43.700 --> 04:45.934
I will not pardon him.

04:46.000 --> 04:47.767
I won't
pardon him yet.

04:47.834 --> 04:51.000
We'll let the smoke clear,
wait a few months,

04:51.066 --> 04:53.200
then we'll get him out.

04:53.266 --> 04:54.734
- Why send him here?

04:54.800 --> 04:57.467
Put Loewen in a nice,
cushy minimum security prison

04:57.533 --> 04:59.934
like Hecht or Macarthur.

05:00.000 --> 05:01.800
- That won't
placate the mob.

05:01.867 --> 05:03.200
They want the mayor
to suffer.

05:03.266 --> 05:05.300
- The most important thing
is to keep him safe.

05:05.367 --> 05:08.900
What's the safest place
in this charnel house?

05:08.967 --> 05:10.834
- Unit J.

05:10.900 --> 05:13.667
Primarily we put bad cops there
so they don't face retaliation

05:13.734 --> 05:15.700
by the rest
of the community.

05:15.767 --> 05:17.200
- Who's in that
cell block now?

05:17.266 --> 05:19.867
- Alvin Yood,
Tobias Beecher.

05:19.934 --> 05:21.800
- Are either
of them black?

05:23.066 --> 05:25.266
- No.

05:25.333 --> 05:27.066
- Okay.

05:27.133 --> 05:29.233
Well, hear this.

05:29.300 --> 05:32.667
Wilson Loewen
is my friend.

05:32.734 --> 05:38.033
Anything happens
to him, Leo, anything,

05:38.100 --> 05:40.934
I will burn this building
to the ground.

05:50.767 --> 05:52.900
- Mayor Loewen.

05:52.967 --> 05:54.233
- Hello, Leo.

05:54.300 --> 05:57.633
The last time I saw you
was at the big fund-raiser

05:57.700 --> 05:59.266
in Morrisville
back when you were

05:59.333 --> 06:00.600
running for
lieutenant governor.

06:00.667 --> 06:04.867
We brought in a shitload
of cash that night, huh?

06:04.934 --> 06:07.066
I was disappointed when
you dropped out of the race.

06:07.133 --> 06:09.233
I always thought you had the
makings of a fine politician.

06:09.300 --> 06:13.333
- Look, whatever relationship
we may have had in the past,

06:13.400 --> 06:15.100
that's over.

06:15.166 --> 06:17.734
You're my prisoner now.

06:18.734 --> 06:20.734
- That simple, huh?

06:20.800 --> 06:23.200
Or do you think I actually
killed those little girls?

06:23.266 --> 06:24.533
- You were found guilty.

06:24.600 --> 06:27.266
- Well, as a black man,

06:27.333 --> 06:29.900
you ought to know
that don't mean dick.

06:29.967 --> 06:32.433
- Take his honor
to Unit J.

06:32.500 --> 06:34.533
- Thank you, friend.

06:40.834 --> 06:42.467
male reporter: The streets are
once again calm,

06:42.533 --> 06:44.567
though the damage
to the east side

06:44.633 --> 06:46.934
due to the rioting is
estimated at $13.7 million.

06:47.000 --> 06:48.900
- Lockdown is over!

06:48.967 --> 06:50.367
- About fuckin' time.

06:50.433 --> 06:52.500
Phelan, where'd they
put Wilson Loewen?

06:52.567 --> 06:54.266
- Don't know.

06:54.333 --> 06:55.800
Probably Unit J.

06:55.867 --> 06:57.600
- J?
Shit.

06:57.667 --> 06:59.100
- Let me
the fuck out!

06:59.166 --> 07:00.867
- Shut up, Cutler,
I'm coming.

07:00.934 --> 07:02.633
- Beecher's in J.

07:02.700 --> 07:05.500
He'll try to hurt the mayor
to get back at me.

07:05.567 --> 07:08.767
I want you to put
the word out, Winthrop.

07:08.834 --> 07:10.233
I want Beecher to know

07:10.300 --> 07:13.066
he better not touch a hair
on the old man's head.

07:16.233 --> 07:18.700
- We were in the oval office
and the president says to me,

07:18.767 --> 07:20.900
"Wilson,
if it weren't for you,

07:20.967 --> 07:22.433
I wouldn't be sitting
in this chair."

07:22.500 --> 07:24.900
And he gave me
these cuff links, see.

07:24.967 --> 07:26.867
Got the presidential
shield on them.

07:26.934 --> 07:29.000
- Mr. Mayor, you're
the only one I know

07:29.066 --> 07:30.934
with a bigger
appetite than me.

07:31.000 --> 07:32.266
- Appetite...

07:32.333 --> 07:33.834
Yeah, for power.

07:33.900 --> 07:36.400
I hear you're not gonna
resign from office.

07:36.467 --> 07:38.100
You're forcing the city council
to vote you out?

07:38.166 --> 07:41.200
- Well, the Honorable
James Michael Curley

07:41.266 --> 07:43.867
served the good people of Boston
while he was incarcerated.

07:43.934 --> 07:47.133
Hell, he even won re-election
while sitting in stir.

07:47.200 --> 07:48.700
I could do
the same thing.

07:48.767 --> 07:50.266
The people love me.
I might run for governor.

07:50.333 --> 07:52.333
- Hell, why not
run for God?

07:58.033 --> 08:01.133
- Hmm...

08:01.700 --> 08:02.934
- What the hell?

08:11.734 --> 08:13.600
- Oh, Jesus.

08:16.734 --> 08:18.367
- How are you doin'?
Can you talk?

08:18.433 --> 08:20.333
- Oh, yeah,
I'm all right, I just...

08:20.400 --> 08:22.934
Choked on...

08:23.000 --> 08:25.600
- He gave him
the Heimlich Maneuver.

08:26.367 --> 08:27.800
- He what?

08:27.867 --> 08:30.333
- Beecher saved
Loewen's life.

08:35.233 --> 08:36.633
- What does Schillinger
want with me?

08:36.700 --> 08:39.100
- I think it's better
if he tells you himself.

08:39.166 --> 08:42.533
- I don't want to hear
anymore of his lies.

08:42.600 --> 08:44.266
You know, this is probably
just some trap

08:44.333 --> 08:45.734
to fuck with
my parole hearing tomorrow.

08:45.800 --> 08:48.000
- I'll admit Schillinger
has conned me in the past,

08:48.066 --> 08:49.600
same as you,
but I--

08:49.667 --> 08:52.000
this time
it's different.

08:56.166 --> 08:58.400
- Beecher.

08:58.467 --> 09:00.333
- What do you want?

09:02.934 --> 09:06.667
- Wilson Loewen has always
been there for my family,

09:06.734 --> 09:07.867
for me.

09:09.333 --> 09:11.100
When my pop
couldn't find work,

09:11.166 --> 09:12.867
he gave him a job
in the parks department.

09:12.934 --> 09:16.033
When Martha and I couldn't
afford a honeymoon,

09:16.100 --> 09:18.700
he gave us airline tickets.

09:18.767 --> 09:20.266
The man is my hero.

09:20.333 --> 09:21.934
You saved his life.

09:22.000 --> 09:24.934
I am now indebted to you.

09:25.000 --> 09:27.533
So, I want you to know

09:27.600 --> 09:30.900
that I won't do anything
to try and stop your parole.

09:30.967 --> 09:34.500
If you can get out
of this fuck hole...

09:34.567 --> 09:36.633
Go.

09:40.900 --> 09:43.367
- Bullshit.

09:43.433 --> 09:45.467
Whatever you're selling,
Vern, I'm not buying.

09:45.533 --> 09:47.367
You grateful to me?

09:47.433 --> 09:49.333
- It's true.

09:49.400 --> 09:50.734
- True?

09:50.800 --> 09:54.867
I can give you a list
as big as my tattooed ass

09:54.934 --> 09:56.467
of things you said were true.

09:56.533 --> 09:58.467
Do I have to stay here?

09:58.533 --> 10:00.066
- No.

10:00.133 --> 10:02.667
- Beecher, if my backing off
wasn't what you were after,

10:02.734 --> 10:04.500
why'd you save Loewen?

10:06.166 --> 10:09.300
- Because I saw
a man dying,

10:09.367 --> 10:12.800
and my instinct was
to save his life,

10:12.867 --> 10:15.066
my gut instinct.

10:15.133 --> 10:19.166
After all these years in Oz,
I still have that instinct.

10:19.233 --> 10:22.066
That's something you
don't know shit about.

10:23.967 --> 10:27.433
- Due to recent circumstances,
the death of your father,

10:27.500 --> 10:29.834
your saving
a fellow inmate's life,

10:29.900 --> 10:32.567
as well as your continued
outstanding behavior,

10:32.633 --> 10:37.133
the board has decided
to grant you parole.

10:38.500 --> 10:40.166
You're a free man,
Mr. Beecher.

10:40.233 --> 10:42.433
The processing
takes a few days,

10:42.500 --> 10:46.400
but for all intents
and purposes, you are free.

10:51.533 --> 10:53.667
- Thank you.
- Good luck.

11:05.367 --> 11:07.500
- Pinch me, sister,
I'm dreaming again.

11:07.567 --> 11:12.900
- No, Tobias,
you are not dreaming.

11:14.166 --> 11:16.100
Oh, oh, oh,
my goodness.

11:16.166 --> 11:17.567
- Holy fuckin' Christ!

11:17.633 --> 11:19.233
- Oh, my God!

11:20.700 --> 11:22.567
- Oh, my God.

11:25.934 --> 11:29.000
- Yo, Lopresti, my lawyer was
supposed to be here an hour ago.

11:29.066 --> 11:30.633
Can you call down
and find out what's going on?

11:30.700 --> 11:32.033
- You haven't heard?

11:32.100 --> 11:34.233
- Heard what?

11:34.300 --> 11:36.467
- I got good news
and I got bad news.

11:36.533 --> 11:40.367
The bad news is
Beecher's father's dead.

11:40.433 --> 11:43.066
- No.

11:43.133 --> 11:47.433
- The day we went into lockdown,
murdered right down the hall.

11:47.500 --> 11:49.900
I guess that puts
a kink in your appeal.

11:54.200 --> 11:55.967
- What's the good news?

11:56.033 --> 11:58.767
- Your girlfriend
got paroled.

11:58.834 --> 12:01.967
That's right,
Beecher's going home,

12:02.033 --> 12:05.900
and from what I hear,
he's in such a hurry to leave,

12:05.967 --> 12:10.233
he won't even have time
to come say bye-bye.

12:21.300 --> 12:22.900
- You know
what they say?

12:22.967 --> 12:24.867
When one of
your senses fails,

12:24.934 --> 12:27.066
the other ones compensate
by getting stronger.

12:27.133 --> 12:28.734
Like if you go blind,

12:28.800 --> 12:30.900
your hearing
suddenly perks up.

12:30.967 --> 12:32.834
Can't smell?

12:32.900 --> 12:34.400
Your taste buds bloom.

12:34.467 --> 12:37.133
So what happens
if you lost them all,

12:37.200 --> 12:40.734
if things no longer
make any sense?

12:40.800 --> 12:44.166
You've got to rely on others
to get you through the day,

12:44.233 --> 12:49.500
and in Oz,
that could be dangerous.

12:49.567 --> 12:52.400
- Rise and shine,
you little fucks!

12:52.467 --> 12:54.500
Get up!

12:54.567 --> 12:56.000
- I can't, I'm sick.

12:56.066 --> 12:57.400
- Bullshit.

12:57.467 --> 13:00.266
If you think you're taking
a siesta in the hospital

13:00.333 --> 13:02.934
just because White did,
you're in for a rude awakening.

13:03.000 --> 13:05.967
Now, get the fuck up.

13:11.066 --> 13:13.333
Oh, Jesus.

13:13.400 --> 13:15.500
- Claire, we got
a problem over here.

13:15.567 --> 13:20.100
- What the fuck
is this, Ebola?

13:22.033 --> 13:23.967
- Fuck you, Martinez.

13:24.033 --> 13:25.734
- Un di voy
a meterlo en su culo.

13:25.800 --> 13:28.166
- Yeah, yeah, yeah,
cha, cha, cha yourself.

13:28.233 --> 13:29.834
- Fuck you, all right?

13:29.900 --> 13:31.533
- You better calm down,
Mr. Martinez,

13:31.600 --> 13:33.400
or I will put you
in restraints.

13:33.467 --> 13:35.834
- What is he,
the nurse's pet?

13:36.967 --> 13:39.800
- Glynn, Nathan won't
give me more painkillers.

13:39.867 --> 13:42.266
- So, call the A.M.A.

13:47.433 --> 13:49.166
What's the emergency?

13:49.233 --> 13:51.000
- Penders, White and Martinez

13:51.066 --> 13:52.533
have methylene chloride
poisoning.

13:52.600 --> 13:54.433
- Did someone
poison them?

13:54.500 --> 13:56.800
- Not someone, us.
- What?

13:56.867 --> 13:58.834
- Oz itself.

13:58.900 --> 14:01.567
Methylene chloride's
found in aerosols,

14:01.633 --> 14:05.333
paint removers, metal cleaning
products, polyurethane,

14:05.400 --> 14:08.000
basically everything that
was used to rebuild this place.

14:08.066 --> 14:10.233
And guess where all
the residue settled?

14:10.300 --> 14:11.934
- In solitary.

14:12.000 --> 14:13.367
Shit.

14:13.433 --> 14:15.967
So, what's the prognosis?

14:16.033 --> 14:17.934
- Well, when caught early,
treatable respiratory

14:18.000 --> 14:22.000
and gastric problems,
but these guys, Leo,

14:22.066 --> 14:24.400
it's all they've been
breathing in 24 hours a day.

14:24.467 --> 14:26.700
Martinez's
liver is shot.

14:26.767 --> 14:29.266
Penders and White
have lung damage,

14:29.333 --> 14:32.333
and to say nothing of
the neurophysiological effects.

14:32.400 --> 14:34.367
- These guys are
gonna get crazy?

14:34.433 --> 14:36.133
- Or it may
make them sane.

14:36.200 --> 14:39.166
But Martinez needs treatment
I can't provide.

14:39.233 --> 14:41.166
I'd like to send him
to Benchley Memorial.

14:46.934 --> 14:49.367
No.

14:49.433 --> 14:50.967
- Well, he'll get
better care.

14:51.033 --> 14:54.100
- For the moment,
let's keep this close to home.

14:54.166 --> 14:55.700
- Leo...

14:55.767 --> 14:57.600
- I don't think we need
to spread the word just yet

14:57.667 --> 14:59.266
that Oz is toxic.

14:59.333 --> 15:01.266
- Well, then I want
to go on record.

15:01.333 --> 15:03.233
- You're a good doctor,
Gloria.

15:03.300 --> 15:05.033
You saved Pancamo after
he caught a staph infection.

15:05.100 --> 15:06.734
We didn't go public
with that, did we?

15:06.800 --> 15:09.867
I have faith

15:09.934 --> 15:11.767
that you'll pull
these guys through, too.

15:24.433 --> 15:25.834
- Espire.

15:25.900 --> 15:30.467
Espire.

15:30.533 --> 15:31.967
- Me siento
como una mierda.

15:32.033 --> 15:34.734
- Yo se, yo se.

15:35.867 --> 15:37.433
Don't you knock?

15:37.500 --> 15:39.100
- Sorry.

15:39.166 --> 15:41.367
Didn't think you'd be doing
anything that needed knocking.

15:41.433 --> 15:44.133
I'm here to transfer
Martinez back to solitary.

15:44.200 --> 15:45.934
- He's not going back
to solitary yet.

15:46.000 --> 15:47.066
- That's what
the paperwork says.

15:47.133 --> 15:48.433
- I don't care about
the paperwork.

15:48.500 --> 15:50.100
- Unless you get Glynn
to tell me different,

15:50.166 --> 15:51.633
Martinez is going.

15:51.700 --> 15:53.500
- I'll be right back.

15:54.900 --> 15:56.600
Excuse me.

16:03.834 --> 16:08.400
- So, what ails you,
Martinez, huh?

16:08.467 --> 16:11.133
You gonna die?

16:12.700 --> 16:15.500
Oh, I love it when
you go all silent on me.

16:15.567 --> 16:17.800
But I don't want
you to die,

16:17.867 --> 16:22.867
at least not until you tell me
who paid you to cut my tendon.

16:23.600 --> 16:25.800
And you will
tell me, Carlos,

16:25.867 --> 16:27.700
'cause I have friends
in solitary.

16:27.767 --> 16:29.467
And when you get back there
they're gonna--

16:29.533 --> 16:32.300
- I have the warden on the phone
in my office, line three.

16:33.433 --> 16:35.900
- Buenas noches,
mi amigo.

16:39.000 --> 16:45.133
Hey, you two make
a really cute pair.

16:50.000 --> 16:52.000
- Jackhammer
miss sally style.

16:52.066 --> 16:54.033
And five, and five,

16:54.100 --> 16:57.300
and three, and do-si-do,
and back and forth,

16:57.367 --> 16:59.567
and five, and five,
and two, and three...

16:59.633 --> 17:01.166
- This is the best
"Miss Sally" ever.

17:01.233 --> 17:02.967
- And jump it out
and work those legs...

17:03.033 --> 17:05.433
- Officer Murphy,
I got an ask.

17:05.500 --> 17:07.500
- I'm in no mood
to be tender, Morales.

17:07.567 --> 17:08.900
- I want to shift jobs.

17:08.967 --> 17:11.033
I've been working at mechanicals
since I got to Oz.

17:11.100 --> 17:12.100
I need a change.

17:12.166 --> 17:13.300
- To where?

17:13.367 --> 17:15.100
- I'm thinking hospital.

17:15.166 --> 17:16.867
I got a couple of pals
who are orderlies,

17:16.934 --> 17:18.033
I thought maybe
I could do some good.

17:18.100 --> 17:20.133
- Some good for yourself,
you mean.

17:20.200 --> 17:21.934
What do you think,
I'm an idiot?

